There is also a victory bonus (800,000 euros) and equality (400,000 for each team). Those who arrive in eighths of the final receive three million each, the eight teams who arrive in fourths of the final receive 3.3 million.
The last four teams will each receive 4 million.
And the champion will win 9 million, compared to the 5.2 received by the other finalist.
Thus, for fixed payments, a club will earn at least 7.1 million, and a maximum of 31.2 million.
On the other hand, the Barça seized 2.5 million for winning the Europe Super Cup in August.
But in addition, there are variable payments, to which 337.8 million are devoted.
This money is distributed according to the proportional value of each television market.
The Spanish market is one of the most important, and has four attractive places.
