New tools for car expertise
In these days of bad weather and accidents, car garages are not the only winners.
Every day, thousands of cars that have suffered a disaster are brought back to a garage, where an expert has to assess the damage suffered and the cost of repair.
Each disaster is different, and the calculation of the cost of parts and working time can be a long and complex work.
To calculate by hand the cost of repair between €20,000 and €30,000, including parts and labour may take two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the assistance of the latest IT tools, this would be a matter of minutes.
That is why almost 100% of the experts use such systems.
Service providers and solutions for disaster assessment and maintenance are dedicated to the collection of information provided by manufacturers, and then to treat them and offer them to their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audadex, of the North American group Solera, is the leading company; 80% of the estimates are made with its products.
Other competing companies in the field of evaluation tools and the development of information on the sector are GtMotif and Eurotax.
Working with data provided by manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Audatex's business director, the company in Spain with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them provides information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed continues to increase, so that over the past five years more versions, variants and motorizations have been launched than in the previous fifteen years.
When a new car leaves the market, these companies get to work.
This is a very hard work, because each of the thousand parts of the vehicle must be catalogued and the price entered.
In addition, a "intelligent" graphical image of each model is drawn on which you can click on the different parts of a tourism car.
If this is a massively sold model, work can be ready within a week if the process progresses very quickly.
In the case of a low-selling car, it may take three or four months. Currently, Audadex has full information of 99.2% of the cars marketed in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models, for example, they have information about the Porsche, but not the Ferrari or Lamborghini.
For vehicles in circulation, the figure exceeds 99%.
In order to carry out the work of documentation and database development, Audatex has eight centres distributed worldwide (in Spain, France, Germany, the United States, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each is specialized in certain brands.
The national seat is located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than one hundred technicians (generally mechanical experts) work simultaneously on three computer screens.
Audadex invests 90 million per year to develop these databases.
Each month, 2.5 million data are recorded, and customers receive updates every two days.
The development of this huge flow of information enables these companies to give different uses and to offer various products.
The most frequent application concerns repair and maintenance, but depending on the countries, there are also tools for the management of the scraps or to calculate the venal or residual value of a car.
The only company that has a guide that informs about the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audadex does not propose it in our country, but she does it in the United States.
In view of the products offered by Audadex, it is easy to get an idea of the type of support it can provide to professionals in the sector.
This company offers ten different tools, the lighthouse product being AudaPlus, the standard disaster assessment solution for experts.
There are cars, motorcycles, light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it takes into account the repair time estimated by the manufacturer or the painting scales.
This tool is purchased according to its use, for each estimate.
